    "This complexity arises because, in addition to intricate network dependencies, researchers must face the fact that we can observe outcomes under only a single realized scenario (Holland 1986).",
    "Interference induced by underlying network structures violates the stable unit treatment value assumption (SUTVA), necessitating methods that can disentangle causal relationships in interconnected settings (Imbens and Rubin 2015)."
